description: Enforce CQRS separation with SQL command side and Mongo query side
alwaysApply: true
---

# Vogel CQRS And Data Consistency Rules

- Every write use case must be modeled as `*Command` + `*CommandHandler` and persist through SQL/EF command-side repositories.
- Every read use case must be modeled as `*Query` + `*QueryHandler` and read from Mongo read models/repositories.
- Do not read EF command aggregates directly inside query handlers.
- Do not write Mongo read models from endpoints or ad-hoc flows; use existing domain-event synchronization patterns.
- Treat SQL Server as source of truth for mutations and MongoDB as query projection store.
- Keep query pagination cursor-based; do not introduce page-number/offset pagination unless explicitly requested.
- If a feature changes read-model shape, update synchronization handlers and Mongo projections in the same change set.
